- "top-performing employees" refers to those ranked in the top 3 within their office based on performance score;
- "recently updated their access" means they have an access type of 'update' and an access date after January 1, 2023;
- "top 50% of their office" is determined by the cumulative distribution of performance scores being less than or equal to 0.5.

- 'Top performers' are defined as employees ranked in the top 3 within their department based on performance score;
- The performance score is a metric used to evaluate employee performance;
- The departments are ordered by the number of top performers they have, from highest to lowest.

- 'Shining stars' refers to offices that have at least one high performer;
- 'Highly skilled and content' refers to employees with a performance score > 80 and job satisfaction > 3;
- 'Soaring high' refers to average performance > 80 and average job satisfaction > 3 among the top three employees in the office.

- 'shining stars' refers to employees with high job satisfaction and performance ratings;
- 'exceeding 4' indicates a rating above 4 out of 5, which is considered very good;
- 'Finance Department' is a specific department within the company.

- "Seasoned professionals" refers to employees over 30 years old;
- "High job satisfaction" refers to a job satisfaction score greater than 4;
- "Spread their wings across multiple departments" means they have worked in more than one department.

- "blossoms stand taller than the average" refers to employees whose performance ratings and self-assessments are higher than the respective averages across all employees;
- "eyes of their supervisors" refers to the performance ratings given by managers;
- "own self-reflection" refers to the self-assessment scores provided by the employees.

- "outperforming the average" refers to employees whose performance score is greater than the average performance score of all employees;
- "average level of contentment" refers to the average job satisfaction score;
- "roles" refers to the position name;
- "workplace" refers to the office name;
- "not alone in their success" refers to having more than one employee in the group.

- 'Mid-Level' refers to employees in the middle of the organizational hierarchy;
- 'High ratings' refer to performance ratings greater than 3;
- 'Above-average job satisfaction' refers to an average job satisfaction score greater than 7.

- 'High-performing' refers to employees with a performance score greater than 80;
- 'Satisfied' refers to employees with a job satisfaction score greater than 4;
- 'Current positions' refers to positions where the end date is not set.

- "shining stars" refers to the top three departments based on their performance scores;
- "brilliance" refers to the average performance score;
- The query ranks departments by their average performance scores, which are calculated from employee data.
